---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="FitSet Privacy Policy">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-800">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-4">FitSet Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="italic text-gray-500 mb-6">Effective: May 26, 2026</p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      FitSet is a fitness app that helps you log workouts, track recovery, and
      get AI feedback on your training. This policy explains what we collect and
      how we use it.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      What stays on your device
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Your workout history, routines, measurements, exercise logs, and profile
      (goal, experience, equipment) are stored locally on your device using
      SQLite. We do not have access to this data, and it is not uploaded to our
      servers.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      What is sent to our servers
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      When you use an AI feature, the relevant input is sent to our backend,
      which forwards it to a third-party AI provider for processing.
      Specifically:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>AI Form Check</strong> — the video or frames you record are sent
        for analysis. The video is processed and discarded; we do not store it.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>AI Coach Chat</strong> — your message and a brief context summary
        (e.g., recent workouts, goal) are sent so the coach can respond. We do not
        store chat content on our servers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Routine Generation, Weekly Recap, Exercise Substitution</strong>
        — the inputs needed to generate a response are sent for processing and not
        retained.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4">
      We do not link this data to your identity, and we do not require an
      account.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Third parties</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">AI processing is performed by:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>OpenAI</strong> (
        <a
          href="https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">privacy policy</a
        >)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google (Gemini)</strong> (
        <a
          href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">privacy policy</a
        >)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Replicate</strong> (
        <a
          href="https://replicate.com/privacy"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">privacy policy</a
        >)
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4">
      These providers process your inputs to generate responses. They do not
      receive any identifier that links the input to you.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Diagnostics</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      If crash reporting is enabled in a build, anonymous diagnostic data may be
      sent to <strong>Sentry</strong> to help us fix bugs. This data does not include
      workout content or personal identifiers.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Permissions</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Camera</strong> — used only when you record a set for Form Check.
        Footage is sent for analysis when you initiate it, and is not accessed otherwise.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Notifications</strong> — used to remind you about workouts. You can
        disable them in settings.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Children</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      FitSet is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly collect
      data from them.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Your choices</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Because your data is stored locally, deleting the app deletes your data.
      There is no account to close.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Changes</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      We may update this policy. The effective date above will reflect the
      latest version.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mb-2">
      Questions? Email
      <a
        href="mailto:getvisiblelondon@gmail.com"
        class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">getvisiblelondon@gmail.com</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-500">— FitSet</p>
  </div>
</Layout>
